metadata.name: the wind on his face
metadata.description:
The astronaut had always felt trapped by the rigid routines and protocols of life in space, but today he decided to take a risk. He strapped on his jetpack and soared out into the void, feeling "the wind on his face" and the rush of adrenaline in his veins. For the first time in months, he felt truly alive.













4200x4200, png, mixed media, April '23
